Heat oil in a 3-quart soup pot over high heat until hot. Add potatoes, onion, celery, leek, turnip, carrot, shallots, and garlic. Stir the vegetables around until they begin to cook but don't turn brown. Add the Basic Vegetable Stock and the Bouquet Garni to soup pot. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to simmering and cook for 45 minutes. Add the zucchini, tomatoes, summer squash, and green beans to soup pot. Simmer 15 minutes more. Stir in the vinegar. Season to taste with salt and pepper. If the soup is too thick, stir in a little water or more Basic Vegetable Stock.